From: Johannes Schindelin <johannes.schindelin@gmx.de>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: doc: fix implicit rule build failure

When the .c files are listed as bare prerequisites (without path prefix),
Make matches them against its implicit rules and tries to compile them
directly with $(CC), bypassing automake's rules that include AM_CPPFLAGS.

This causes build failures because config.h and gnutls/gnutls.h cannot
be found:

    gcc printlist.c -o printlist
    printlist.c:21:10: fatal error: config.h: No such file or directory

The upstream history is:

- https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/commit/8daba130 (doc: Fix races
  in a parallel build., 2024-10-30) introduced proper $(srcdir)/
  prefixes and changed the build to use $(MAKE) with proper targets.

- https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/commit/5300a868 (Revert "doc:
  Fix races in a parallel build.", 2024-11-13) reverted it, but
  instead of restoring the 3.8.11 behavior, it introduced bare .c
  file prerequisites that trigger implicit rules.

- https://gitlab.com/gnutls/gnutls/-/commit/5bea8f31 (doc/Makefile:
  re-add three binaries to DISTCLEANFILES, 2026-02-09) partially
  addressed the fallout but did not fix the actual build failure.

Fix this by using $(srcdir)/ prefixed paths, which prevents implicit rule
matching while still tracking the files as dependencies.

Assisted-by: Claude Opus 4.5
Signed-off-by: Johannes Schindelin <johannes.schindelin@gmx.de>
---
 doc/Makefile.am | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/doc/Makefile.am b/doc/Makefile.am
--- a/doc/Makefile.am
+++ b/doc/Makefile.am
@@ -424,9 +424,9 @@ alert_printlist_LDADD = ../lib/libgnutls.la ../gl/libgnu.la
 # Multiple Targets") are not used here since that's a non-POSIX GNU
 # Make extension.
 stamp_error_codes: \
-		$(top_srcdir)/lib/errors.c errcodes.c \
-		$(top_srcdir)/lib/algorithms/ciphers.c printlist.c \
-		$(top_srcdir)/lib/alert.c alert-printlist.c
+		$(top_srcdir)/lib/errors.c $(srcdir)/errcodes.c \
+		$(top_srcdir)/lib/algorithms/ciphers.c $(srcdir)/printlist.c \
+		$(top_srcdir)/lib/alert.c $(srcdir)/alert-printlist.c
 	$(MAKE) $(AM_MAKEFLAGS) errcodes printlist alert-printlist
 	./errcodes > error_codes.texi-tmp
 	mv -f error_codes.texi-tmp error_codes.texi
